<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="447" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dupuy de Lôme</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Philadelphia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-07"><hi rend="italic">October 7,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The lawyer who is in Wilmington, N. C., urging the release of the <hi rend="italic">Commodore</hi> is the same Mr. Reuben Pastner, of B.
                            Guerra, treasurer of the Cuban Junta and one of the counsel for the
                            defendants in the trial at Wilmington, Del.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dupuy de Lôme.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Handed to Mr. Adee by Dr. Gaytan, Secretary of the
                                    Spanish Legation, October 8, 1895.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain in Washington</hi></placeName>[,
                                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-08">undated</date>].</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The Spanish consul in Key West wires that leaders and considerable
                                number of men left the Keys; that the <hi rend="italic">Cincinnati</hi> is in port; that the <hi rend="italic">Woodall</hi> is about to start from New Orleans, conveying the
                                party, and that the <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>, probably now in
                                Key West, is preparing to sail. Consul in Tampa reports expedition
                                is now in Pine Reef.</p>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>